✅ ✅ ✅ COSINE SIMILARITY
✅ Exercise 1
🔹 Code
import torch
import torch.nn.functional as F

v1 = torch.tensor([1.,2.,3.])
v2 = torch.tensor([1.,2.,3.])

print(F.cosine_similarity(v1, v2, dim=0))


🔹 Answer
1 (same vectors)

✅ Exercise 2
🔹 Code
import torch
import torch.nn.functional as F

v1 = torch.tensor([1.0, 0.0])
v2 = torch.tensor([0.0, 1.0])

similarity = F.cosine_similarity(v1, v2, dim=0)

print("Cosine Similarity:", similarity.item())



🔹 Answer
0 (different)


✅ ✅ ✅ TEXT CLASSIFICATION
✅ Exercise 1
🔹 Question
Classify text

🔹 Code
from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import CountVectorizer
from sklearn.naive_bayes import MultinomialNB

texts = ["good movie","bad movie"]
labels = ["Positive","Negative"]

vec = CountVectorizer()
X = vec.fit_transform(texts)

model = MultinomialNB()
model.fit(X, labels)

print(model.predict(vec.transform(["good movie"])))


🔹 Answer
Positive


